---
Exercise 1 - Get or Post:

A user is returning a login name and password.	->	POST
A user is requesting a new page via a hyperlink.	->	GET
A chat room user is sending a written response.	->	POST
A user hits the ‘next’ button to see the next page.	->	GET
A user hits the ‘log out’ button on a secure banking site.	->	POST
A user hits the ‘back’ button on the browser.	->	GET
A user sends a name and address form to the server.	->	POST
A user makes a radio button selection.	->	GET

---
Exercise 2 - Mapping URLs to content:

http://www.wickedlysmart.com
http://www.wickedlysmart.com/skiingAdvice
http://www.wickedlysmart.com/beerAdvice
http://www.wickedlysmart.com/select/selectBeer.html

---

Exercise 3 - Request response:

1. The browser creates an HTTP GET request
2. The HTTP GET is sent to the server
3. The server finds the page
4. And generates an HTTP response
5. The HTTP response is sent to the browser
6. The browser renders the HTML
7. Client reads the page

